        { myth: '"Anyone can get a federal job."', reality: 'Federal hiring is highly competitive + bureaucratic. Veterans get hiring preference. USAJobs is opaque + slow. Pathways Programs (recent grads, students) are the easiest entry.' },
        { myth: '"You can\'t be fired from government."', reality: 'Civil service protection is real but not absolute. Performance-based termination + RIFs (reduction in force) happen. Schedule F + politicization concerns are real ongoing issues.' },
        { myth: '"Government pay is uniformly low."', reality: 'GS-12 to GS-15 federal pay $89K-$184K varies by locality. Senior Executive Service: $150-250K. State + local pay varies dramatically by region. Pension + benefits often more valuable than nominal salary difference suggests.' }
