      demographics: 'Federal workforce ~45% women (varies by agency — civilian DoD more male, HHS more female). Strong racial diversity at GS-7-12 levels, gap at SES + senior. Veterans benefit from hiring preference. Disability hiring program (Schedule A) is a major entry point.',
      entry_picks: { hs: ['postal'], cert: ['parkranger'], associate: ['paralegal', 'courtclerk'], bachelor: ['analystfed', 'foreignservice', 'parkranger', 'electedofficial', 'lawyer', 'cityplanner', 'librarian'], graduate: ['cityplanner', 'librarian', 'museumcurator', 'archivist'], doctoral: ['researcher'], professional: ['lawyer'] },
      journals: ['Federal News Network', 'Government Executive', 'Route Fifty for state/local', 'PA Times'],
