      honest_notes: 'ADHD is the diagnosis where career fit matters more than accommodations. Most ADHD adults thrive in roles with high novelty + meaningful stakes + autonomy + variety. Crisis-response careers (ED, fire, paramedic, trauma surgery, ER psychiatry) often suit ADHD particularly well. Detail-precision roles with no novelty (accounting, archives, paperwork-heavy admin) are where ADHD adults most often burn out, regardless of accommodation quality.'
