      hard_fit_careers: ['surgeon', 'paramedic', 'firefighter', 'detective', 'fbi', 'detective', 'broadcaster', 'flightattendant', 'pilot', 'salesrep'],
      honest_notes: 'Mental health and career fit are bidirectional — wrong-fit careers (chronic burnout, toxic culture, no autonomy) cause mental health collapse; right-fit careers (autonomy, meaning, manageable stakes, supportive culture) protect. The biggest predictor is workplace culture, not job title. Many highly successful professionals in every field navigate chronic conditions privately; the disclosure decision is deeply personal and not always career-advancing.'
