    // \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550
    // PHASE 23: TRAUMA-INFORMED PRACTICE
    // \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550
    if (sub === 'trauma_informed') {
      var tiSection = s.tiSection || 'overview';

      return h('div', { className: 'max-w-3xl mx-auto p-4 md:p-6 space-y-3' },
        backBtn('career', null, 'Career menu'),
        h('h2', { className: 'text-2xl font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83c\udf3f Trauma-Informed Practice'),
        h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-300 leading-relaxed' }, 'Trauma-informed practice = recognizing how widespread trauma is, understanding how trauma affects behavior + learning + relationships, and designing services so they don\'t re-traumatize people. Foundational for educators, healthcare, social services, justice system.'),

        h('div', { className: 'flex flex-wrap gap-1' },
          [
            { key: 'overview', label: '\ud83d\udccb Foundation' },
            { key: 'aces', label: '\ud83d\udcca ACEs research' },
            { key: 'effects', label: '\ud83e\udde0 Trauma effects' },
            { key: 'principles', label: '\u2713 6 principles' },
            { key: 'practice', label: '\ud83d\udee0 In practice' }
          ].map(function(t) {
            return h('button', {
              key: t.key,
              onClick: function() { upd({ tiSection: t.key }); },
              className: 'px-2 py-1.5 rounded text-xs font-bold transition ' + (tiSection === t.key ? 'bg-emerald-600 text-white' : 'bg-slate-700 text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-600')
            }, t.label);
          })
        ),

        tiSection === 'overview' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udccb What "trauma-informed" actually means'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'SAMHSA\'s 4 Rs: (1) Realize the widespread impact of trauma, (2) Recognize signs + symptoms in clients/students, (3) Respond by integrating trauma knowledge into practices, (4) Resist re-traumatization.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Trauma-informed \u2260 trauma-treating: '), 'Trauma-informed is universal precaution \u2014 assume trauma is present + design accordingly. Trauma-treating is specialized therapy (TF-CBT, EMDR, CPT) for diagnosed PTSD/trauma. Different scopes.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Why it matters in education: '), 'A trauma-affected student\'s "behavior problem" often is a survival adaptation. Punishing without addressing the trauma response = re-traumatization. Trauma-informed schools see dramatic reductions in suspensions + improvements in attendance + outcomes.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Why it matters in workplaces: '), '~70% of adults have experienced at least one ACE. Trauma-informed workplaces design with that in mind \u2014 predictable communication, psychological safety, accommodations for triggers, flexibility for treatment.')
        ),

        tiSection === 'aces' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udcca ACEs research base'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'The CDC-Kaiser ACE Study (Felitti, Anda 1998) is foundational. They surveyed 17,000+ adults about childhood adverse experiences + linked to health outcomes 50 years later.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'The 10 original ACEs: '), 'physical, emotional, sexual abuse; physical, emotional neglect; household substance use, mental illness, domestic violence; parental separation/divorce; incarcerated household member.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Key findings: '), 'ACEs are common (~64% of adults have 1+, ~17% have 4+). Cumulative dose effect \u2014 higher ACE score = higher risk for nearly every adverse health + life outcome. ACE 4+ vs ACE 0: ~2x heart disease, ~2x cancer, ~4x depression, ~12x suicide attempts, ~2x stroke, smoking, COPD.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Expanded ACEs: '), 'Newer research adds adverse community experiences (violence, racism, food insecurity, eviction, foster care). These compound + sometimes exceed traditional household-level ACEs.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Critical caveats: '), '(1) ACE score is risk indicator, not destiny \u2014 resilience factors (one stable adult, community, opportunity) moderate. (2) Don\'t weaponize ACE scores against individuals or use as gatekeeping. (3) Indigenous + Black communities have higher community-level ACEs due to historical + ongoing structural violence \u2014 not individual pathology. (4) "Positive Childhood Experiences" (PCEs) are equally important + understudied.')
        ),

        tiSection === 'effects' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83e\udde0 How trauma affects behavior + learning'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Hypervigilance + threat detection: '), 'Trauma-affected brain scans environment for threat constantly. Loud noises, sudden movements, certain voices/tones may trigger stress response. School: kid who "overreacts" to teacher\'s tone may be activated by something reminiscent of past harm.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Dysregulation: '), 'Limbic system on high alert; prefrontal cortex less able to regulate. Big emotional reactions to small triggers. School: meltdown over what looks like minor change.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Difficulty with executive function: '), 'Trauma shifts brain resources to survival, away from planning, working memory, attention. School: "doesn\'t listen," "can\'t focus," "no follow-through" \u2014 often trauma manifesting as ADHD-like symptoms.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Fight, flight, freeze, fawn: '), 'Stress response patterns. Fight = aggression. Flight = avoidance, school refusal. Freeze = dissociation, shutdown. Fawn = appease, compliant but exhausted.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Attachment difficulties: '), 'Hard to trust adults. May seek connection then push away. Hard to form stable peer relationships. May test boundaries to see if adults stick around.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Somatic + health effects: '), 'Headaches, stomachaches, sleep problems, immune suppression. Long-term: increased risk of heart disease, autoimmune conditions, addiction.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Cognitive distortions: '), '"I\'m bad." "No one cares." "It\'s my fault." These shape behavior + relationships.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Triggers: '), 'Specific stimuli (sounds, smells, people, places) that reactivate trauma response. Often the person doesn\'t know why they\'re reacting \u2014 sub-cortical processing.')
          )
        ),

        tiSection === 'principles' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\u2713 SAMHSA 6 principles of trauma-informed care'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-3 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '1. Safety: '), 'Physical + psychological safety. Predictable environments, clear expectations, freedom from violence + threats. For schools: anti-bullying, restorative practices, clear (non-arbitrary) rules.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '2. Trustworthiness + transparency: '), 'Decisions made openly, consistent follow-through, honest communication about what will happen + why. Don\'t surprise people with painful information; explain processes.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '3. Peer support: '), 'Connection with others who have lived experience. Reduces isolation + shame. In schools: support groups, mentor programs. In workplaces: ERGs.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '4. Collaboration + mutuality: '), 'Power-sharing in relationships. Student/client has voice + choice. Recognize provider-recipient dynamics + work to flatten.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '5. Empowerment, voice, choice: '), 'Help people recognize + build on strengths. Offer meaningful choices. Resilience-focused not deficit-focused.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, '6. Cultural, historical + gender issues: '), 'Recognize that trauma is experienced + processed differently by culture, gender, history of oppression. Avoid colorblind or one-size-fits-all approaches.')
          )
        ),

        tiSection === 'practice' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udee0 Trauma-informed practice tools'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Reframe "what\'s wrong with you?" to "what happened to you?": '), 'Foundational mindset shift. Behavior is communication; trauma-informed practitioners ask "what need is this behavior meeting?" before "how do I stop this behavior?"'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Co-regulation: '), 'Adult regulates first; child borrows the regulation. Calm presence, slow breathing, soft voice, predictable response. The dysregulated brain doesn\'t learn from yelling.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Predictability + structure: '), 'Visual schedules, advance notice of changes, consistent routines. Reduces threat-detection load.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Choice + autonomy: '), 'Even small choices ("red or blue paper?") restore sense of agency. Critical for traumatized people who experienced powerlessness.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Sensory regulation: '), 'Fidgets, weighted blankets, low lighting options, sensory breaks. Body-level regulation supports brain-level learning.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Restorative discipline: '), 'Repair harm through dialogue + accountability rather than punishment. Restorative circles, mediation, restitution.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Mindfulness + grounding: '), '5-4-3-2-1 grounding (5 things you see, 4 hear, 3 feel, 2 smell, 1 taste). Box breathing. Body scans. Brings prefrontal cortex back online.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Take care of your own nervous system: '), 'Secondary traumatic stress is real for educators + first responders + therapists. Supervision, peer support, time off, your own therapy.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Build resilience factors: '), 'One stable adult relationship is the strongest protective factor. Be that adult. Reliable, present, not perfect.')
          )
        )
      );
    }

    // \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550
    // PHASE 24: CULTURAL COMPETENCE PRACTITIONER GUIDE
    // \u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550\u2550
    if (sub === 'cultural') {
      var cuSection = s.cuSection || 'overview';

      return h('div', { className: 'max-w-3xl mx-auto p-4 md:p-6 space-y-3' },
        backBtn('career', null, 'Career menu'),
        h('h2', { className: 'text-2xl font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83c\udf0d Cultural Competence + Cultural Humility'),
        h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-300 leading-relaxed' }, 'Cultural competence is foundational for any practitioner whose work involves people. The field has moved from "competence" (mastery framing) toward "humility" (lifelong learning) \u2014 but both have value. This primer covers the contemporary practitioner approach.'),

        h('div', { className: 'flex flex-wrap gap-1' },
          [
            { key: 'overview', label: '\ud83d\udccb Foundations' },
            { key: 'humility', label: '\ud83d\ude4f Cultural humility' },
            { key: 'specific', label: '\ud83d\udc65 By population' },
            { key: 'language', label: '\ud83d\udde3 Language access' },
            { key: 'pitfalls', label: '\u26a0 Common pitfalls' }
          ].map(function(t) {
            return h('button', {
              key: t.key,
              onClick: function() { upd({ cuSection: t.key }); },
              className: 'px-2 py-1.5 rounded text-xs font-bold transition ' + (cuSection === t.key ? 'bg-emerald-600 text-white' : 'bg-slate-700 text-slate-200 hover:bg-slate-600')
            }, t.label);
          })
        ),

        cuSection === 'overview' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udccb Why cultural competence matters in assessment + service'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Assessment instruments are culturally biased: '), 'Most psychological + educational tests were developed using White, middle-class, US samples. Norms, content, presumed background knowledge all reflect that. Misinterpretation across cultures is common + harmful.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Help-seeking varies culturally: '), 'Mental health stigma, family-centered vs individual orientation, religious frameworks, language of distress all vary. "Depression" is conceptualized + reported differently across cultures.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Treatment engagement varies culturally: '), 'Western individual psychotherapy is one approach. Family-based, religious, somatic, community approaches all valid. Insisting on Western evidence-based practice may alienate clients who need other paths.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Disparities are real + measurable: '), 'Black children diagnosed with disability at higher rates with worse outcomes. Latino children under-identified. Asian American mental health under-utilized. Indigenous children removed from families at extreme rates.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'You\'re also a cultural being: '), 'Your own race, ethnicity, religion, class, sexuality, gender, ability shape your assumptions + reactions. Cultural competence starts with self-awareness, not just learning about "them."')
          )
        ),

        cuSection === 'humility' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\ude4f Cultural humility (Tervalon + Murray-Garc\u00eda 1998)'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Cultural humility was proposed as alternative to cultural competence. Three pillars:'),
          h('ol', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed list-decimal pl-5' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Lifelong learning + critical self-reflection: '), 'No one is ever fully "competent" in cultures other than their own. The work is continuous self-examination + learning.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Recognizing + challenging power imbalances: '), 'Practitioner-client relationship inherently has power dynamics. Cross-cultural relationships compound this. Conscious effort to share power, listen, honor client expertise.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Institutional accountability: '), 'Individual cultural humility is necessary but insufficient. Institutions must change \u2014 policies, practices, hiring, training, accountability structures.')
          ),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Key practical shift: '), 'From "I know enough about your culture to help you" to "Tell me what I need to understand about your context to help you well." Center client as expert on their own life.'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed mt-2' }, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Combined: '), 'Best practice integrates both. Cultural competence (knowledge about populations) AND cultural humility (self-reflection + power-sharing + lifelong learning).')
        ),

        cuSection === 'specific' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-3' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udc65 Practice considerations by population (introductory)'),
          h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-amber-300 italic' }, '\u26a0 These are starting points, not stereotypes. Individual variation within any group is enormous. Use as conversation-openers, not assumptions.'),
          h('div', { className: 'space-y-3' },
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'African American / Black communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Historical trauma (slavery, Jim Crow, ongoing structural racism). Justified mistrust of medical + educational systems (Tuskegee, Henrietta Lacks, Larry P.). Church + extended family often central. Mental health stigma in some communities + reframed as spiritual/character issue. Strength-based approaches resonate.')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Latino / Hispanic communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Familismo (family centrality), respeto (respect for elders + authority), simpat\u00eda (harmonious interaction). Mental health may be expressed somatically. Religious + folk healing traditions common. EL students should be assessed in language of strength. National origin matters (Mexican, Puerto Rican, Dominican, Cuban, Central + South American all different).')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Asian American + Pacific Islander communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Vast diversity (East, Southeast, South Asian; Pacific Islander). Mental health stigma + face-saving concerns common. Family obligation + collective identity strong. "Model minority" myth obscures struggle + diversity. Refugee communities (Vietnamese, Cambodian, Hmong, Burmese) have specific trauma histories.')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Indigenous + Native American communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, '574 federally recognized tribes + many unrecognized. Historical + ongoing trauma (genocide, boarding schools, land theft, sovereignty violations). Connection to land, language, ceremony central to many. ICWA + tribal sovereignty matter. Specific protocols for working with tribal communities (consult IHS or tribal authorities for guidance).')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Refugee + immigrant communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Pre-migration trauma + post-migration stress. Language barriers + cultural transitions. May avoid government systems due to status concerns. Specific groups (Somali, Syrian, Afghan, Ukrainian) have unique histories. Use trained interpreters; never family members for clinical content.')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'LGBTQ+ communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Minority stress framework \u2014 chronic stress from stigma + discrimination drives mental health disparities, not the identity itself. Family rejection is huge risk factor; family acceptance protective. Pronouns + name use matter clinically. Trans youth + adults face specific medical + social challenges; gender-affirming care is evidence-based.')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Religious + spiritual communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Spirituality is often a strength + resource, not a barrier. Don\'t assume religious clients are conservative or vice versa. Specific traditions (Evangelical Christianity, Catholicism, Islam, Judaism, Hinduism, Buddhism, etc.) have specific values + concerns. Ask + don\'t assume.')
            ),
            h('div', { className: 'p-3 rounded bg-slate-900/60' },
              h('h4', { className: 'text-xs font-black text-emerald-300 mb-1' }, 'Rural communities'),
              h('p', { className: 'text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' }, 'Independence + self-reliance valued. Mental health services often scarce + stigmatized. Travel distance to providers significant. Telehealth has been transformative. Don\'t bring urban assumptions about resources or values.')
            )
          )
        ),

        cuSection === 'language' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-800/60 border border-emerald-500/30 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-emerald-200' }, '\ud83d\udde3 Language access + working with interpreters'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Title VI civil rights: '), 'Federal law requires language access in any program receiving federal funding. Schools + healthcare + government must provide interpretation.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Never use family as interpreters: '), 'Especially children. Confidentiality + family dynamics + concept translation all suffer. Some content (mental health, sexual health, legal) is inappropriate for family. Trained professional interpreters required.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Professional medical/legal interpreter standards: '), 'NCMI (National Council on Interpreting in Health Care), Certification Commission for Healthcare Interpreters, court interpreter certification. Trained interpreters know confidentiality, accuracy, neutrality requirements.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Working with interpreters effectively: '), 'Brief interpreter beforehand. Speak directly to client (not "tell her..."). Pause for translation. Avoid idioms + slang. Use short sentences. Check for understanding. Plan extra time (sessions often 2x as long).'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Telephonic + VRI interpreters: '), 'Available 24/7. Useful for low-incidence languages. Less ideal for clinical work than in-person but better than no interpretation.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Bilingual practitioners: '), 'Even more valuable than interpreters. Conduct sessions directly. Native-level vs conversational fluency matters; some bilingual practitioners overestimate their clinical-language capacity.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Translated written materials: '), 'Required under Title VI for "frequently encountered" languages. Translation isn\'t neutral \u2014 concepts that don\'t exist or have different meanings need cultural adaptation, not just direct translation.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-emerald-300' }, 'Sign language: '), 'ASL is full language, not "translation of English." Deaf clients have right to ASL interpreter. VRS for phone. Many Deaf clients prefer Deaf interpreter (DI) for high-stakes interactions.')
          )
        ),

        cuSection === 'pitfalls' && h('section', { className: 'p-4 rounded-xl bg-rose-900/20 border border-rose-500/40 space-y-2' },
          h('h3', { className: 'text-sm font-black text-rose-200' }, '\u26a0 Common cultural competence pitfalls'),
          h('ul', { className: 'space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-100 leading-relaxed' },
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, '"I don\'t see color/race/etc.": '), 'Colorblindness ignores documented disparities + invalidates clients\' experiences. Race + culture are real + matter.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Treating culture as monolithic: '), '"Black culture," "Asian culture" aren\'t single things. Individual variation within any group is enormous. Avoid stereotypes even positive ones.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Cultural fragmenting: '), 'Reducing client to single identity (their disability, race, religion). People are intersectional + whole.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Performative competence: '), 'Diversity training certificate without behavior change. Cultural awareness without institutional change.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Assuming you can\'t serve clients of different background: '), 'Cross-cultural clinical work is possible + often necessary. Cultural humility + ongoing learning enable it. Don\'t use background-mismatch as excuse.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'White-savior framing: '), 'Mission to "help" marginalized communities without their leadership or input. Center community voices + leadership.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Cultural appropriation in practice: '), 'Using practices (mindfulness, smudging, etc.) divorced from cultural context can be harmful + offensive. Honor origins + tradition holders.'),
            h('li', null, h('strong', { className: 'text-rose-300' }, 'Ignoring structural causes: '), 'Trauma + poverty + discrimination cause mental health issues for many. Treating individual without addressing systemic causes = limited help.')
          )
        )
      );
    }

